However, as he was being led in handcuffs and shackles out of the courtroom, the teenager told a swarm of reporters he was 'sorry.'

Lane's parents and sister, who had read heartbreaking victim impact statements before the verdict was announced, expressed satisfaction with the outcome of the trial. 

'This naughty boy is never going to do this to any other family,' Donna Lane told the media, according to Sydney Morning News. 

A co-defendant in the case, James 'Bug' Edwards Jr., now 17, testified that he was a passenger in the car when it swerved toward Lane, and Luna fired the shot. 

Edwards testified as part of a plea agreement in which a first-degree murder charge against him was reduced to being an accessory after the fact.

